1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:00,838
In this lecture

2
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:02,625
we will introduce Docker

3
00:00:03,125 --> 00:00:08,125
a platform designed to simplify application development and deployment by using containerization

4
00:00:08,512 --> 00:00:14,375
Docker allows developers to package applications along with their dependencies into containers

5
00:00:14,750 --> 00:00:17,825
ensuring consistency across multiple environments

6
00:00:18,212 --> 00:00:20,062
A Docker container is a lightweight

7
00:00:20,337 --> 00:00:21,125
standalone

8
00:00:21,375 --> 00:00:25,837
and executable package that incorporates everything needed to run a piece of software

9
00:00:26,212 --> 00:00:27,688
including the application code

10
00:00:28,125 --> 00:00:28,762
runtime

11
00:00:28,975 --> 00:00:29,925
system tools

12
00:00:30,125 --> 00:00:30,975
and libraries

13
00:00:31,363 --> 00:00:35,325
This characteristic makes it an essential tool for modern DevOps practices

14
00:00:35,688 --> 00:00:39,987
enabling seamless collaboration between development and operations teams

